		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>Your gaze causes foodstuffs to become inedible, a wood door to rot, armor to grow brittle, or a weapon to rust.</i></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Encounter</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Minor Action</b><b> &#8226; </b><b>Ranged</b> 10</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Target:</b> One object </p><p><b>Effect:</b> The target gains vulnerability to all damage equal to one-half your level + your Intelligence modifier until the end of your next turn. If the target is a weapon, attacks with it take a penalty to damage rolls equal your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1) until the end of your next turn. If the target is armor, a creature wearing it takes a -2 penalty to AC until the end of your next turn. </p><p>Published in Dragon Magazine 387, page(s) 55. </p>",
